    "reasoning": "To implement a sequence detector for '1101', I will use a Finite State Machine (FSM). \n1. **State Definitions**: \n   - `S_IDLE`: Initial state, looking for the first '1'.\n   - `S_1`: Found '1', looking for the second '1'.\n   - `S_11`: Found '11', looking for '0'.\n   - `S_110`: Found '110', looking for '1'.\n   - `S_FOUND`: The sequence '1101' has been detected. Once in this state, the output `start_shifting` remains 1 forever until reset.\n2. **FSM Logic**:\n   - From `S_IDLE`: If `data == 1`, go to `S_1`; else stay `S_IDLE`.\n   - From `S_1`: If `data == 1`, go to `S_11`; else go to `S_IDLE`.\n   - From `S_11`: If `data == 0`, go to `S_110`; else stay `S_11` (since '111' still contains '11').\n   - From `S_110`: If `data == 1`, go to `S_FOUND`; else go to `S_IDLE`.\n   - From `S_FOUND`: Stay in `S_FOUND` regardless of input.\n3. **Output Logic**: `start_shifting` is 1 if the state is `S_FOUND`, otherwise 0. However, the spec says 'set start_shifting to 1, forever, until reset'. This implies the output itself acts like a latch or the state machine enters a terminal state.\n4. **Reset**: Synchronous active-high reset. On reset, state returns to `S_IDLE` and `start_shifting` is 0.\n5. **Advice to avoid syntax errors**: \n   - Always use `always @(*)` for combinational blocks to avoid missing signals in the sensitivity list.\n   - Ensure all paths in a `case` statement are covered or provide a `default` to prevent unintended latches.\n   - Use `logic` for all signal declarations to adhere to SystemVerilog standards.",
    "module": "module TopModule(\n    input  logic clk,\n    input  logic reset,\n    input  logic data,\n    output logic start_shifting\n);\n\n    // State encoding\n    localparam logic [2:0] S_IDLE   = 3'b000;\n    localparam logic [2:0] S_1     = 3'b001;\n    localparam logic [2:0] S_11    = 3'b010;\n    localparam logic [2:0] S_110   = 3'b011;\n    localparam logic [2:0] S_FOUND = 3'b100;\n\n    // State registers\n    logic [2:0] current_state;\n    logic [2:0] next_state;\n\n    // Sequential logic for state transition\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (reset) begin\n            current_state <= S_IDLE;\n        end else begin\n            current_state <= next_state;\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Combinational logic for next state\n    always @(*) begin\n        next_state = current_state;\n        case (current_state)\n            S_IDLE:\n                if (data == 1'b1) \n                    next_state = S_1;\n                else \n                    next_state = S_IDLE;\n            \n            S_1:\n                if (data == 1'b1) \n                    next_state = S_11;\n                else \n                    next_state = S_IDLE;\n            \n            S_11:\n                if (data == 1'b0) \n                    next_state = S_110;\n                else \n                    next_state = S_11;\n            \n            S_110:\n                if (data == 1'b1) \n                    next_state = S_FOUND;\n                else \n                    next_state = S_IDLE;\n            \n            S_FOUND:\n                next_state = S_FOUND;\n            \n            default:\n                next_state = S_IDLE;\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // Output logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        if (current_state == S_FOUND) begin\n            start_shifting = 1'b1;\n        end else begin\n            start_shifting = 1'b0;\n        end\n    end\n\nendmodule"
